The paper deals with crowd counting in images, which is a computer vision problem, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The proposed method involves the use of a rescaling module and classification process, which suggests the involvement of machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) also likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of benchmarks and evaluation metrics, indicating the involvement of multimedia techniques, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of image processing techniques to address the challenges of crowd counting, which suggests the involvement of information retrieval techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category as well.
